

Key Performance Indicator #1: Which Politicians Speak the most truthfully and the most unthrufully

<img width="1201" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/abf7b9ed-33e7-4142-9a50-21b4056d61f6" />

This visualisation shows that George W. Bush is the politician who spoke the most untruthfully at each of his press conferences. The Politicial who spoke the most truthfully was John Anderson. The data is colour coded and showed on the figure as a number, with each speakers total "points" being added.
